article.headline: Charlotte 74, Rhode Island 64
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Leemire Goldwire scored 34 points and Lamont Mack added 19 to lead Charlotte to a 74-64 win over Rhode Island on Saturday night. Goldwire connected on 10-of-21 from the floor, including 6-of-13 from 3-point range, and went 8-for-8 from the line to lead the 49ers to their fourth win in their last five games. Kahiem Seawright led the Rams (21-10, 7-9 Atlantic 10) with 17 points and 15 rebounds. Rhode Island led 38-35 at halftime, but the 49ers (18-12, 9-7) used a 13-2 run early in the second half to surge ahead 59-50. The Rams closed to within 61-58 with 4:27 left on a pair of free throws by Lamonte Ulmer. But Goldwire, who tied a school record for most games in a season with 30 points with six, knocked down a 3-pointer with 2:21 to go, giving Charlotte a 66-59 lead. The Rams, who lost five of their last six, shot 34 percent from the field, and just 3-of-21 from 3-point range.
